WEBVTT

00:01.520 --> 00:04.160
Here you go, little hatchling.

00:04.600 --> 00:07.160
Ooh, it's gonna be so snuggly.

00:07.240 --> 00:10.120
[exclaiming in disgust]
Let's get rid of that.

00:10.240 --> 00:11.960
Little one.

00:16.360 --> 00:17.360
Amy?

00:17.960 --> 00:19.000
Amy!

00:21.200 --> 00:22.960
Oh.

00:23.040 --> 00:26.720
I know what's going on. [chuckles]

00:26.920 --> 00:30.400
A sneaky game of hide-and-seek. [chuckles]

00:30.680 --> 00:34.320
Well, little did you know,
I am an expert at hide-and-seek,

00:34.400 --> 00:36.880
because of my alcoholic wife. [laughs]

00:41.160 --> 00:42.320
[Paula] Sorry, it's no children.

00:42.400 --> 00:44.280
What? It's not a child, it's a baby.

00:44.360 --> 00:46.400
Well, there's references
to suicide and all sorts,

00:46.520 --> 00:48.440
-so I'm afraid it's an adults-only event.
-My mum's in there

00:48.520 --> 00:50.120
and I just wanted to say hello.
She wrote the book.

00:50.200 --> 00:51.720
-Not with that baby.
-It's a baby.

00:51.840 --> 00:53.840
She doesn't understand
anything you're saying. She can't read.

00:53.960 --> 00:56.320
-Is it 18 years old?
-Is this baby 18 years old?

00:56.400 --> 00:57.240
-Yes.
-No.

00:57.320 --> 00:58.960
-So it's not allowed.
-Okay, fine.

00:59.240 --> 01:00.600
-This lovely lady...
-What are you doing?

01:00.920 --> 01:01.920
-Er, no.
-...is going to look after you...

01:02.000 --> 01:03.200
-Oh. No.
-...for a bit. Thank you.

01:03.280 --> 01:04.760
Er, excuse me? No.

01:06.880 --> 01:08.000
[baby yelps]

01:08.200 --> 01:12.120
Sneaky, cheeky hide-and-seek-y.

01:12.200 --> 01:14.320
Ah-ha! [chuckles]

01:14.560 --> 01:15.520
Ha!

01:16.040 --> 01:16.880
Ah-ha!

01:18.840 --> 01:20.080
[muttering excitedly]

01:20.200 --> 01:22.400
Like your husband, I found
the medication very helpful.

01:22.480 --> 01:23.320
Yes, good.

01:23.400 --> 01:26.080
But obviously, you never know
when the darkness is going to descend,

01:26.160 --> 01:29.080
so, my question was actually about salmon.

01:29.400 --> 01:30.280
Oh. Yes.

01:30.360 --> 01:32.560
'Cause you're saying that the fatty acids
are good for the brain.

01:32.640 --> 01:33.480
[Amy] Excuse me.
[Deborah] That's right.

01:33.560 --> 01:35.560
-[Dennis] I don't like, er, salmon.
-Hey, Mum.

01:36.520 --> 01:37.840
-Amy, what are you doing here?
-I need to talk to you

01:37.920 --> 01:40.280
-about <i>The Baumgaertner Trick.</i>
-Okay. Just give me a second.

01:40.400 --> 01:41.680
-I need to talk to you now.
-Are you alright?

01:41.920 --> 01:43.400
-Why have you--
-I'm fine. I just need to talk to you.

01:43.520 --> 01:45.280
-Okay, just give me two seconds.
-I'll be over here.

01:45.360 --> 01:46.240
I'm working.

01:48.320 --> 01:49.760
So, salmon.

01:50.200 --> 01:53.120
-[all chanting] M-Dog. M-Dog. M-Dog.
-[Shun] Mr Flowers.

01:54.520 --> 01:56.680
Well done, well done, well done.

01:56.800 --> 01:58.560
[all cheering]

01:59.520 --> 02:02.400
Stay in your seat, you imbecile!
I said belts on!

02:02.680 --> 02:04.440
-I'm so sorry about all this.
-It's alright.

02:04.520 --> 02:07.320
And then, it starts to get weird
and you realise you've been

02:07.400 --> 02:08.920
collecting hundreds of bottles--

02:09.000 --> 02:10.200
Yes. Do you mind just giving me two ticks,

02:10.280 --> 02:11.680
-so I can say a quick hello to my--
-[sighs]

02:11.760 --> 02:12.880
[Dennis] 'Cause you're going to learn
how to brew...

02:12.960 --> 02:13.960
Come on.

02:14.040 --> 02:16.440
...elderflower champagne and start
an international catering business,

02:16.520 --> 02:17.680
and it's like, erm...

02:18.560 --> 02:21.360
-It's actually quite mad, isn't it?
-Er, not mad. Ill. [chuckles]

02:22.160 --> 02:25.240
[Dennis] Then it gets a bit bleak again.
I start feeling like shit.

02:26.920 --> 02:29.320
Walking across bridges. [shivering] Erm,

02:29.960 --> 02:30.800
back to the doctor's.

02:30.920 --> 02:32.360
-Your grandad...
-[gunshot]

02:32.840 --> 02:34.160
Baumgaertner.

02:34.720 --> 02:35.720
<i>Baumgaertner.</i>

02:36.320 --> 02:37.680
<i>Baumgaertner.</i>

02:38.080 --> 02:39.480
<i>Baumgaertner.</i>

02:40.800 --> 02:43.600
[Wendy] Die AuserwÃ¤hlte. <i>The Chosen One.</i>
<i>It's German.</i>

02:43.680 --> 02:45.600
<i>When it gets dark</i>
<i>I turn into a butterfly...</i>

02:45.760 --> 02:48.760
What do you think I should do?
Because I don't have a girlfriend, so...

02:49.720 --> 02:50.840
What do you think I should do?

02:51.800 --> 02:53.640
I, erm, I... I don't know.

02:54.520 --> 02:57.600
I'm sorry. Erm,
we're not actually together anymore, so...

02:58.760 --> 02:59.960
Oh, what the fuck.

03:00.640 --> 03:02.520
[Maurice] <i>Everyone. Everyone. A toast...</i>

03:02.920 --> 03:06.160
to the most loyal,
patient, beautiful friend,

03:06.440 --> 03:07.280
Shunny Boy.

03:07.560 --> 03:09.360
-[all cheering]
-Shunny boy!

03:09.480 --> 03:10.920
[all chanting] Shun. Shun. Shun.

03:11.280 --> 03:12.520
You are my friend as well.

03:12.600 --> 03:13.520
I love you.

03:13.640 --> 03:15.280
I wanted to let loose, but it was obvious

03:15.360 --> 03:18.840
these squidiot dickheads would
get wasted and trashed

03:18.920 --> 03:20.520
and there'd be no one
to drive home safely.

03:20.640 --> 03:22.240
My wife showed me how to do this.

03:23.720 --> 03:25.360
You're quite responsible, aren't you?

03:26.360 --> 03:29.040
-I guess so, yeah.
-Team M-Dog!

03:29.440 --> 03:31.120
Hence drinking Naked Russians all night.

03:31.680 --> 03:33.440
-Do you mean milk?
-[Donald] Well...

03:34.120 --> 03:35.080
