04:16.000 --> 04:17.080
Oh, you wish!

04:17.800 --> 04:19.280
Dad, shut up and fuck off, please!

04:19.400 --> 04:21.040
Who do you want to play it with then, Don?

04:21.120 --> 04:23.680
I know answer. Matilda cha.

04:23.800 --> 04:26.040
-Fuck off!
-[all cheering]

04:27.800 --> 04:28.800
Fuck off, Shun!

04:29.080 --> 04:29.920
Sushi head!

04:30.720 --> 04:32.120
[tyres screeching]

04:33.080 --> 04:36.120
Shut up! Or I'm not driving!
I don't even fancy her!

04:36.680 --> 04:38.440
She's just a customer
and I felt sorry for her

04:38.680 --> 04:40.720
because she's poor and her house is shit.

04:40.960 --> 04:42.400
She used to be fat.

04:42.920 --> 04:44.600
She's Fat Matilda.

04:44.680 --> 04:47.120
[chuckling] Of course I don't fancy her.

04:49.760 --> 04:50.920
God's sake.

04:53.560 --> 04:54.520
[Barry] <i>Amy?</i>

04:57.400 --> 04:59.920
I don't want to come in
if you're in your smalls.

05:02.160 --> 05:03.840
Little baby?

05:04.440 --> 05:07.720
Are you in there
with your auntie Amy, huh?

05:11.040 --> 05:11.880
Come on.

05:13.160 --> 05:14.840
Right. Erm,

05:15.040 --> 05:16.440
put your dressing gown on.

05:17.240 --> 05:18.600
I'm coming in.

05:38.080 --> 05:39.960
-[baby crying]
-[Amy shushing]

05:41.920 --> 05:43.640
[distorted laughter]

06:08.400 --> 06:10.240
[Bolero] I wouldn't eat those
if I were you, love.

06:11.080 --> 06:12.160
Catch the plague.

06:13.480 --> 06:15.640
They've been marinated in piss,

06:15.880 --> 06:18.120
all sorts for about a hundred years.

06:20.520 --> 06:22.720
What's a nice-looking
young mother like you

06:22.800 --> 06:24.240
doing in a place like this?

06:24.800 --> 06:25.800
Looking for a job?

06:26.160 --> 06:27.280
Oh, no.

06:27.720 --> 06:28.880
I'm not a prostitute.

06:32.560 --> 06:33.400
[chuckles]

06:34.920 --> 06:36.320
[glass shatters]

06:38.320 --> 06:39.720
You're meant to catch that.

06:41.280 --> 06:42.440
Is Wendy here?

06:43.760 --> 06:45.000
Some jingle-jangle.

06:46.160 --> 06:47.360
For the intel.

07:26.600 --> 07:29.040
[cheers and applause]

07:59.360 --> 08:00.320
Barry?

08:03.240 --> 08:04.120
Barry?

08:05.240 --> 08:06.680
Barry, can I see my baby?

08:07.000 --> 08:09.120
[stammers] I don't think
you should come in.

08:09.480 --> 08:11.520
She's sleeping very soundly.

08:11.760 --> 08:14.000
Honestly. I, I, I'll take care of it.

08:14.200 --> 08:15.640
Can I just come in, though?

08:16.760 --> 08:19.160
[mimics baby crying] Aw. [shushing]

08:19.480 --> 08:21.040
It's alright, little one.

08:22.400 --> 08:24.200
You nearly woke her then.

08:24.720 --> 08:26.880
[gagging]

08:27.160 --> 08:28.040
Shit.

08:33.280 --> 08:34.640
[Barry trembling]

08:35.480 --> 08:36.320
What have I done?

08:38.000 --> 08:40.400
Come on, Barry, come on, think.

08:47.000 --> 08:48.320
What's your favourite film?

08:49.720 --> 08:52.560
Erm, don't know. What's yours?

08:53.320 --> 08:54.480
Probably cling film.

08:56.760 --> 08:59.720
No. <i>Age Of Machines,</i> obviously. Brilliant.

09:01.200 --> 09:02.960
Yeah. I might head off in a minute.

09:03.400 --> 09:04.240
Already?

09:04.800 --> 09:06.800
I was just about to engage party mode.

09:07.000 --> 09:07.960
Bit tired.

09:08.400 --> 09:10.720
Okay. Well, can I give you a lift?

09:11.120 --> 09:12.200
Er, no, it's alright.

09:12.560 --> 09:13.720
I'm still under the limit.

09:14.560 --> 09:15.640
Okay, whatever.

09:18.760 --> 09:19.960
Whoa. What are you doing?

09:20.200 --> 09:21.280
What are you doing?

09:23.840 --> 09:24.720
Sorry!

09:28.240 --> 09:29.200
[Maurice] Shun?

09:32.440 --> 09:33.440
Alright.

09:38.080 --> 09:40.120
So your family died in an earthquake?

09:41.840 --> 09:42.760
Mm-hmm.

09:44.440 --> 09:47.160
There I am,
taking all my shit out on your bum hole.

10:00.440 --> 10:01.720
I just need to check something.

10:03.320 --> 10:05.000
You're not going
to press charges, are you?

10:06.080 --> 10:06.920
What?

10:07.080 --> 10:09.040
For... just then.

10:09.480 --> 10:10.800
When I tried to kiss you.

10:11.920 --> 10:13.920
Erm, no.

10:14.680 --> 10:15.640
Don't worry.

10:15.720 --> 10:17.920
Okay. Good.

10:18.720 --> 10:19.560
Because...

10:20.440 --> 10:21.800
I just assumed.

10:34.040 --> 10:35.680
-What are you doing now?
-What?

10:36.080 --> 10:37.360
I just need to know
that if I try and kiss you,

10:37.440 --> 10:38.480
you're not going to move away again.

10:38.560 --> 10:40.240
Well, what do you want? A signed document?

10:40.360 --> 10:42.280
-So you do want to?
-Just forget it.

10:42.400 --> 10:43.560
Oh, God. Make your mind up.

10:43.640 --> 10:45.320
I don't know how I feel about you.

10:45.400 --> 10:46.680
I don't know how I feel about you, mate.

10:46.920 --> 10:49.880
One minute you're Queen Frigid-Lips,
the next minute you're a fat slag again.

10:51.720 --> 10:54.440
Right. Good. Okay.

10:55.120 --> 10:56.800
I do know how I feel about you, actually.

10:57.960 --> 10:58.840
Bye.

10:59.720 --> 11:01.520
Oh. Thanks for fixing my sink.

11:03.400 --> 11:04.520
Twat!

11:06.200 --> 11:07.040
[Maurice] Shun.

11:07.280 --> 11:08.560
[dance music playing]

11:09.120 --> 11:10.000
[Shun] Yes?

11:10.920 --> 11:12.240
Is this Bulgarian?

11:12.560 --> 11:14.400
Yeah, just put it all in a big bowl.

11:14.480 --> 11:16.040
Shun, baby dawg.

11:16.240 --> 11:20.480
Er, put it all in a big bowl for these
fine young ladies, if you please.

11:20.560 --> 11:22.560
Excuse me. Excusez-moi.

11:22.800 --> 11:25.440
Sorry. [chuckling]

11:26.040 --> 11:27.800
-Yeah. This is what--
-[glass shattering]

11:27.880 --> 11:29.240
-Yes.
-[Dolores] M-Dog.

11:29.320 --> 11:31.640
[cheering]

11:31.720 --> 11:33.920
Woooo-hooo-whooo.

11:36.880 --> 11:39.440
Erm, excuse me.
I'm going to need that for next time.

11:39.560 --> 11:41.280
-It's cardboard.
-I know.

11:41.640 --> 11:43.840
I was going to recycle it but... Oh.

11:43.920 --> 11:45.400
Do you know what, you just keep it.

11:45.600 --> 11:48.040
-Well, I don't want it, it's rubbish.
-Well, then throw it away.

11:48.640 --> 11:50.000
Well, if anything I'll recycle it.

11:59.720 --> 12:00.680
Hi.

12:03.240 --> 12:04.160
Hello.

12:08.640 --> 12:10.320
-Er, how did it go?
-Erm,

12:10.440 --> 12:11.960
not very well, thank you very much.

12:12.120 --> 12:14.640
I think Amy might've already gone,
so, er, if you came to see her--

12:14.840 --> 12:16.280
I assume you're not here for me.

12:16.400 --> 12:17.720
Not here for you, no.

12:18.000 --> 12:19.280
Well, you should probably go home then.

12:19.360 --> 12:20.840
I mean, I'm here to see you.

12:21.000 --> 12:23.160
Just not for you, if you know what I mean.

12:23.520 --> 12:26.080
Hylda, I'm sorry about the other day,
but I'm just, I'm going to get a kebab

12:26.240 --> 12:28.440
and I'm going to go home.
So could we, maybe do this another time?

12:28.560 --> 12:31.800
-'Cause it's been a horrible day.
-Oh. Why is that, then?

12:31.880 --> 12:33.800
Because I'm not qualified
to have written this book.

12:34.000 --> 12:34.840
Every time I try
and make something better,

12:34.920 --> 12:36.880
I just make it worse, Hylda.
I just make it worse.

12:36.960 --> 12:39.920
And, er, look, I know I was rude
the other day, but she's my baby.

12:40.000 --> 12:41.400
She's my little squiggle.

12:41.480 --> 12:42.960
Donald was the squoggle
and she's the squiggle,

12:43.040 --> 12:45.640
and, erm, you're just not what I expected,
that's all.

12:45.840 --> 12:48.240
Erm, and with Amy,
I've sort of given up trying to...

12:48.320 --> 12:49.520
I've sort of given up trying to...

12:50.280 --> 12:51.840
Could I maybe, erm...

12:52.840 --> 12:53.840
give you a lift?

12:54.640 --> 12:56.200
[Paula] Sorry, just, erm...

12:56.600 --> 12:58.400
do you actually want this or not?

12:58.560 --> 13:00.880
Because I just spoke to Carol
and she told me to pulp it.

13:05.560 --> 13:08.440
[Wendy] It's not a cult, and I'm not
a witch, and I never slept with him.

13:08.600 --> 13:10.680
Though your grandad did
fool around quite a bit.

13:10.840 --> 13:12.800
So did your nana.
I take it you know about James?

13:12.920 --> 13:14.560
But why did you call me <i>Die Auserwahlte?</i>

13:14.680 --> 13:16.520
Oh, that, yeah,
just amusing meself, really.

13:16.600 --> 13:18.640
I just, I need you to tell me
about The Baumgaertner Trick.

13:18.760 --> 13:21.480
What, that it wasn't a trick gun?
Of course it was a trick gun.

13:21.560 --> 13:23.000
Spread that rumour himself, the pillock.

13:23.120 --> 13:25.360
-No. What?
-You mean the Russian Roulette trick?

13:25.440 --> 13:27.160
Here, look. Bring the baba.

13:27.600 --> 13:29.320
Fucking terrible magician.

13:30.000 --> 13:32.440
Brilliant showman,
but constantly fucking everything up.

13:32.640 --> 13:34.720
Nearly sawed poor little Harriet in half.

13:34.800 --> 13:37.680
Possibly on purpose. Who knows?
Look at all this crap.

13:41.720 --> 13:42.560
Bingo.

13:44.400 --> 13:47.880
He'd finish the trick by shooting a vase.
Bit of a flourish.

13:48.080 --> 13:50.200
But he had such a terrible aim
that in the end

13:50.400 --> 13:52.280
he put a little banger in with the roses

13:52.520 --> 13:54.080
and set it off with a little wire.

13:54.160 --> 13:55.760
No bullets in the gun at all.

13:58.400 --> 14:00.600
Shouting at the Devil
like he was in the room.

14:01.240 --> 14:04.440
Going on and on about
how he was going to break the curse.

14:04.720 --> 14:05.840
Bendy Wendy, he used to call me.

14:06.400 --> 14:08.920
This lot waltz in here,
chuck their kit off.

14:09.200 --> 14:12.160
I have to fold myself into a cocoon,
for crying out loud.

14:12.240 --> 14:13.720
Hang on. Could I show you something?

14:13.800 --> 14:15.880
This was in the suitcase you gave me.
What is it?

14:15.960 --> 14:16.920
Ah.

14:18.960 --> 14:20.480
Bum Gardener.

14:21.000 --> 14:22.440
I remember him talking about this.

14:22.560 --> 14:24.040
-What, what'd you mean?
-Yeah,

14:24.120 --> 14:25.640
around the time he went to the asylum.

14:25.880 --> 14:27.200
What asylum? He drowned.

14:27.440 --> 14:28.680
Drowned? Nah.

14:28.760 --> 14:31.480
Harriet told little Maurice
he'd performed a vanishing act.

14:31.560 --> 14:33.720
He didn't buy it,
so she told him he drowned.

14:33.800 --> 14:34.840
So he didn't die?

14:35.720 --> 14:37.480
Well, he died eventually.

14:37.720 --> 14:40.440
Last I heard, went to Germany.
Popped his clogs there.

14:40.520 --> 14:43.120
What are you talking about?
What is this book?

14:43.200 --> 14:44.800
Why am I <i>Die AuserwÃ¤hlte?</i>

14:44.880 --> 14:47.320
You do know
Felix changed his name, don't ya?

14:48.120 --> 14:50.680
From Baumgaertner.

14:51.480 --> 14:54.080
'Cause it sounded
too much like Bum Gardener.

14:55.880 --> 14:57.880
His grandmother painted these, darling.

14:59.080 --> 15:00.600
This is your family.

15:01.520 --> 15:02.760
<i>Die AuserwÃ¤hlte.</i>

15:19.280 --> 15:20.240
Where do you want it?

15:20.680 --> 15:21.560
Thank you.

15:21.760 --> 15:22.920
Yes, I'll just, erm...

15:24.880 --> 15:26.920
Okay. Thank you for the kebab.

15:27.920 --> 15:30.120
-Erm...
-Oh, I'm hungry.

15:31.760 --> 15:33.040
What did you say this was again?

15:33.720 --> 15:35.040
Oh, Fizzy Shizz.

15:35.440 --> 15:36.320
It's nice.

15:36.800 --> 15:38.080
That one's grapefruit.

15:38.840 --> 15:40.400
Grapefruit Grenade.

15:40.840 --> 15:42.800
Yes, well, I'll try it. Okay.

15:42.880 --> 15:44.640
Amy gives me a hard time about it.

15:44.720 --> 15:47.400
-Wreaks havoc with your insides.
-Okay.

15:47.480 --> 15:49.080
-Alright. See you soon.
-Erm,

15:49.320 --> 15:50.520
er, Deborah.

15:51.600 --> 15:53.120
Yeah, er...

15:53.960 --> 15:55.240
the thing is, it's just...

15:55.640 --> 15:59.440
I had a couple of questions
I wanted to ask you about Amy.

16:01.440 --> 16:02.360
Erm...

16:04.040 --> 16:06.560
I'm an addict,
so I know how to talk to addicts.

16:06.640 --> 16:08.640
